Creational Patterns (Object Creation)
-------------------------------------
Singleton - Ensure only ONE instance exists globally (e.g., database connection pool)
Factory Method - Subclasses decide WHICH object to create (e.g., DocumentFactory → PDF/Word/Excel)
Abstract Factory - Factory of factories - creates FAMILIES of related objects (e.g., UIFactory → Windows/Mac buttons+scrollbars)
Builder - Construct complex objects STEP-BY-STEP with fluent API (e.g., StringBuilder, HttpRequest.newBuilder())
Prototype - CLONE existing objects instead of creating new (e.g., object.clone())


Structural Patterns (Object Composition)
----------------------------------------
Adapter - Convert one INTERFACE to another (e.g., Arrays.asList() adapts array to List)
Bridge - SEPARATE abstraction from implementation (e.g., Remote → TV/Radio, independent hierarchies)
Composite - TREE structure where leaf and composite treated uniformly (e.g., File/Folder hierarchy)
Decorator - ADD behavior dynamically by WRAPPING (e.g., BufferedReader(FileReader), coffee + milk + sugar)
Facade - Simple UNIFIED interface to complex subsystem (e.g., OrderService hides payment/inventory/shipping)
Flyweight - SHARE common state to save memory (e.g., String pool, chess pieces sharing color/type)
Proxy - PLACEHOLDER that controls access to real object (e.g., lazy loading, caching, access control)


Behavioral Patterns (Object Interaction)
----------------------------------------
Chain of Responsibility - PASS request along handler chain until processed (e.g., logging levels, servlet filters)
Command - ENCAPSULATE request as object with execute() (e.g., button click actions, undo/redo)
Iterator - TRAVERSE collection without exposing internals (e.g., for-each, List.iterator())
Mediator - CENTRALIZE complex communications (e.g., chat room coordinates user messages)
Memento - CAPTURE object state for undo/restore (e.g., editor snapshots, game save points)
Observer - NOTIFY multiple objects when state changes (e.g., event listeners, pub-sub, MVC)
State - CHANGE behavior when internal state changes (e.g., TCP connection: Listen/Established/Closed)
Strategy - SWAP algorithms at runtime (e.g., Collections.sort(comparator), payment methods)
Template Method - DEFINE skeleton, subclasses override steps (e.g., AbstractList, Spring's JdbcTemplate)
Visitor - ADD new operations without modifying classes (e.g., AST traversal, tax calculation on different products)